yajl-fort
------------------------------------------
The YAJL-Fort package provides a modern object-oriented Fortran interface to
the YAJL C library, which is an event-driven parser for JSON data streams.
JSON is an open standard data interchange format. It is lightweight, easy for
humans to read and write, and language independent.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libgfortran5-13.4.0-1
  libyajl2-2.1.0-1
  libyajl_fort-devel-1.4-1bl1
  libyajl_fort1-1.4-1bl1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-fortran-13.4.0-1
  libyajl-devel-2.1.0-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/nncarlson/yajl-fort

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/nncarlson/yajl-fort/archive/refs/tags/v1.4.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack yajl-fort-1.4-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./yajl-fort-1.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/yajl-fort-1.4-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/yajl-fort-1.4-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libyajl_fort1-1.4-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libyajl_fort-devel-1.4-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(yajl-fort)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/yajl-fort.README
  /usr/share/doc/yajl-fort/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/yajl-fort/README.md

(libyajl_fort1)
  /usr/bin/cygyajl_fort-1.dll

(libyajl_fort-devel)
  /usr/include/yajl/json.mod
  /usr/include/yajl/yajl_fort.mod
  /usr/lib/libyajl_fort.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/yajl-fort.pc

